<!-- §11 How to use -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">How to Install and Use the WiFi Smart DIY Music Neon Light Strip</h2>

<div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 1: Plan Your Layout</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Measure your space and decide on the 5m or 10m version. Sketch where the strip will run—along walls, ceiling cove, behind TV, around desk edges, or creating shapes. The DIY shapeable design means you can bend it around corners and curves. Clean the surface where you'll install it (dust-free is essential for adhesive).</p>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 2: Power and WiFi Setup</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Choose the correct plug standard for your region (American, European, Australian, or English). Plug the controller into power. Download the Vibe Strip app on your smartphone. The app will prompt you to connect to your home WiFi. Once connected, the controller syncs with your phone via WiFi and Bluetooth.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 3: Install the Strip</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Peel back a small section of the adhesive backing. Carefully place the strip at your starting point, pressing firmly. Work your way along the entire length, following your planned route. Press firmly into any corners or curves. Let the adhesive set for 24 hours before flexing or adjusting the strip.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius);">
    <div style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem;">Step 4: Customize Colors, Scenes, and Music Sync</div>
    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.5;">Open the app and select individual LED sections to assign custom colors. Create gradients by selecting a range and blending colors smoothly. Set up scene presets (e.g., "gaming red," "chill blue," "party rainbow"). Enable music-responsive mode to sync colors to audio. Your strip will now respond to beats, rhythms, and frequency changes in real time. Save your favorite setups for quick switching.</p>
  </div>
</div>

