<!-- FAQ -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">What makes RGBIC different from regular RGB?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">RGBIC stands for RGB + Integrated Circuit. Each LED has its own control chip, meaning every single LED can be set to a different color independently. Regular RGB strips control all LEDs as one unit—they're all the same color. RGBIC enables gradients, animations, and sophisticated effects that regular RGB can't achieve. This is why this strip costs more but delivers so much more creative control.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Does the music-responsive feature actually work well?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes, it's genuinely impressive. The app listens to audio playing through your phone and syncs LED colors to beats, rhythm, and frequency spectrum. Works best with streaming apps and live audio. The sync is responsive and creates real visual impact, especially with energetic music like EDM, hip-hop, or electronic. Perfect for gaming streams and content creation where synchronized lighting adds production value.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Should I get the 5m or 10m version?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">5m (300 LEDs) covers a small room perimeter or one accent wall. 10m (960 LEDs) wraps full walls or creates bolder statements. Consider your space: if you're lighting a desk corner or one wall, 5m is plenty. For full-room coverage or gaming cave setups, 10m makes a bigger impact. More LEDs = higher visual density and more customization options, but also higher cost and installation complexity. Start with 5m unless you have a large room or want intensive coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I control it without WiFi?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes. The strip supports both WiFi and Bluetooth. WiFi gives you remote app control from anywhere in your home (or globally with some setups). Bluetooth works within range (typically 30 feet) without requiring a network. You can use Bluetooth-only if you want local control without WiFi, though WiFi is more convenient for full features. Both modes work, so choose based on your connectivity needs.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How does it compare to static neon wall decor?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Static neon (like the Neon Light Wall Decor at $49–57) is a fixed design—usually a symbol, shape, or phrase in one color that stays the same. The WiFi strip is dynamic: colors change, animate, sync to music, and respond to your input. You pay more ($105+) for control and customization. Pick static neon if you want simplicity and a specific aesthetic. Pick the WiFi strip if you want creative freedom and responsiveness.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Is installation difficult?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Moderate difficulty. The strip is self-adhesive, so you peel, position, and press. The main challenge is planning the route (especially around corners and curves) and ensuring the surface is clean and dust-free before sticking. Installation takes 30–60 minutes depending on length and layout. No special tools or technical knowledge needed, but patience and careful measurement help. Give yourself time and don't rush it.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">What's the power consumption?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The 5m version draws approximately 50W max when all LEDs are at full brightness. The 10m version draws around 100W max. Both include a power adapter for your regional plug standard. Just plug into any standard outlet—no special electrical setup required. Power consumption is moderate and safe for standard residential circuits.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Does it work with voice assistants like Alexa or Google Home?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Not currently. You control it via the mobile app. Voice assistant integration may be added in future updates, but as of now, rely on the app for all control and customization. This is a limitation compared to some smart home lighting systems. If voice control is essential, this may not be the best fit.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How long does the adhesive last?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">The adhesive is designed for permanent installation on clean, smooth surfaces. It typically lasts for years without peeling. However, if you need to remove or reposition the strip, the adhesive may not stick again. Plan your installation carefully before sticking. If the surface becomes dust-laden or the strip starts to lift, you can reinforce with additional adhesive strips or mounting hardware.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Can I cut the strip to a specific length?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">Yes, most RGBIC strips can be cut at designated cut points marked on the strip. After cutting, you lose the portion beyond the last LED. Plan your layout carefully before cutting to avoid waste. Each cut section needs its own controller if you want independent control.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">Will the colors look vibrant on white vs. colored walls?</summary>
    <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">
      <p style="margin: 0;">White walls provide the best color clarity and reflection. Colored walls will blend with the LED colors—a blue wall with red LEDs looks purple. Dark walls absorb more light, so the same LEDs appear dimmer. Install on white surfaces or ceilings for maximum visual impact.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details style="padding: 1rem; background: var(--muted); border-radius: var(--radius); cursor: pointer;">
    <summary style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--foreground); user-select: none;">How many presets and custom effects are available?</summary>
